The peculiar difficulty os Persius consiste in the arrangement of the dialogus or supposed dialogus. There are also a few passages which perhaps no editor has yet satisfactorily explained. I think Mr. Maeleane has handled the matter well, though he may be mistalren sometimes. I agree with what he says of Jahn's copious commentary.
